fields.description: The fork identifier. Set to zero if no fork is active.

fields.name: chainId
fields.description: The chain ID of the current fork.

fields.name: chainInfo
fields.description: The chain and fork the access occurred.

fields.name: kind
fields.description:
The kind of account access that determines what the account is.
 If kind is Call, DelegateCall, StaticCall or CallCode, then the account is the callee.
 If kind is Create, then the account is the newly created account.
 If kind is SelfDestruct, then the account is the selfdestruct recipient.
 If kind is a Resume, then account represents a account context that has resumed.

fields.name: account
fields.description:
The account that was accessed.
 It's either the account created, callee or a selfdestruct recipient for CREATE, CALL or SELFDESTRUCT.

fields.name: accessor
fields.description: What accessed the account.

fields.name: initialized
fields.description:
If the account was initialized or empty prior to the access.
 An account is considered initialized if it has code, a
 non-zero nonce, or a non-zero balance.

fields.name: oldBalance
fields.description: The previous balance of the accessed account.

fields.name: newBalance
fields.description:
The potential new balance of the accessed account.
 That is, all balance changes are recorded here, even if reverts occurred.

fields.name: deployedCode
fields.description: Code of the account deployed by CREATE.

fields.name: value
fields.description: Value passed along with the account access

fields.name: data
fields.description: Input data provided to the CREATE or CALL

fields.name: reverted
fields.description: If this access reverted in either the current or parent context.

fields.name: storageAccesses
fields.description: An ordered list of storage accesses made during an account access operation.

fields.name: depth
fields.description: Call depth traversed during the recording of state differences

fields.name: account
fields.description: The account whose storage was accessed.

fields.name: slot
fields.description: The slot that was accessed.

fields.name: isWrite
fields.description: If the access was a write.

fields.name: previousValue
fields.description: The previous value of the slot.

fields.name: newValue
fields.description: The new value of the slot.

fields.name: reverted
fields.description: If the access was reverted.

Returns a compact signature (`r`, `vs`) as per EIP-2098, where `vs` encodes both the
signature's `s` value, and the recovery id `v` in a single bytes32.
This format reduces the signature size from 65 to 64 bytes.
func.declaration: function signCompact(Wallet calldata wallet, bytes32 digest) external returns (bytes32 r, bytes32 vs);

func.description:
Signs `digest` with `privateKey` using the secp256k1 curve.
Returns a compact signature (`r`, `vs`) as per EIP-2098, where `vs` encodes both the
signature's `s` value, and the recovery id `v` in a single bytes32.
This format reduces the signature size from 65 to 64 bytes.
func.declaration: function signCompact(uint256 privateKey, bytes32 digest) external pure returns (bytes32 r, bytes32 vs);

func.description:
Signs `digest` with signer provided to script using the secp256k1 curve.
Returns a compact signature (`r`, `vs`) as per EIP-2098, where `vs` encodes both the
signature's `s` value, and the recovery id `v` in a single bytes32.
This format reduces the signature size from 65 to 64 bytes.
If `--sender` is provided, the signer with provided address is used, otherwise,
if exactly one signer is provided to the script, that signer is used.
Raises error if signer passed through `--sender` does not match any unlocked signers or
if `--sender` is not provided and not exactly one signer is passed to the script.
func.declaration: function signCompact(bytes32 digest) external pure returns (bytes32 r, bytes32 vs);

func.description:
Signs `digest` with signer provided to script using the secp256k1 curve.
Returns a compact signature (`r`, `vs`) as per EIP-2098, where `vs` encodes both the
signature's `s` value, and the recovery id `v` in a single bytes32.
This format reduces the signature size from 65 to 64 bytes.
Raises error if none of the signers passed into the script have provided address.
func.declaration: function signCompact(address signer, bytes32 digest) external pure returns (bytes32 r, bytes32 vs);

func.description:
Has all subsequent calls (at this call depth only) create transactions that can later be signed and sent onchain.
Broadcasting address is determined by checking the following in order:
1. If `--sender` argument was provided, that address is used.
2. If exactly one signer (e.g. private key, hw wallet, keystore) is set when `forge broadcast` is invoked, that signer is used.
3. Otherwise, default foundry sender (1804c8AB1F12E6bbf3894d4083f33e07309d1f38) is used.
func.declaration: function startBroadcast() external;
